{
  "doc_id": "16178",
  "text": "For the problems of propagation of electromagnetic waves, a very efficient closure mechanism was introduced by Bérenger [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . He proposed to surround the computational domain by a layer of artificial material computations, in particular, because often by the time it manifests itself the phase errors would have already killed the solution [CITATION_3] . We tend to believe, however, that the deterioration of solution due to the phase errors is not always that rapid (Section 3), and as any potentially adverse phenomenon, the long-term instability of the PMLs needs to be carefully addressed.",
